post_text: This week we found Wanda on a trail near the Matterhorn in the Swiss Alps. One of the best-known mountains in the Alps, the Matterhorn is located near the Swiss-Italian border, 6 miles (10 kilometers) southwest of Zermatt, Switzerland. The mountain, called Mont Cervin in French and Monte Cervino in Italian, is 14,691 feet (4,478 meters) high, and its peak dominates the town of Zermatt as well as the surrounding area. Click the link below to fly over the Matterhorn. https://youtu.be/tYuXTJJMkaY

post_text: Earlier today a book was posted on our district social media platform with a title with a culturally insensitive reference. We were unaware of this reference and meant no offense or harm. As soon as it was brought to our attention that this book title had offensive implications, the post was immediately removed from our feed. We are grateful to those in our community who hold our district accountable and appreciate the community members who took the time to educate us on this reference. Again, we deeply apologize and strive to do better.
